ed_at": "2021-05-17T11:52:54Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I am doing a twisted mass-rebase of several 10k branches. This involves re-annexing 100k files (i.e. change their content and put it back into the annex). This starts with a fresh clone:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndatalad clone --reckless ephemeral ria+file:///...ce3f3fffe fixup\r\n```\r\n\r\nI need the `ephemeral` for efficiency reasons.\r\n\r\nNow I am facing this problem:\r\n\r\n```\r\n% git commit -a --amend --no-edit\r\nerror: invalid object 100644 91e15dc904225126970a8cb35912e5b0db053875 for '000/021/MD5E-s53\r\n32849--bae29652c989fa1234daf4b7c44d1360.tar.gz.log'                                       \r\nfatal: git-write-tree: error building trees                                               \r\ngit-annex: failed to read sha from git write-tree                                          \r\nCallStack (from HasCallStack):                                                            \r\n  error, called at ./Git/Sha.hs:23:15 in main:Git.Sha                                     \r\n```\r\n\r\nI am not sure where this is coming from, but I suspect it is happening, because I have more than one clone like this, and maybe the sharing of git objects (default with local clones) breaks the operation due to undesired interactions.\r\n\r\nAnyways, this particular issue points to a more general issue: there is no way to customize the `clone` call (e.g. with `--no-local`, but there are more that can have relevance in special cases).\r\n\r\nOption specification seems to be implemented all the way up to `clone_dataset()`, so it is accessible for internal use, but not in general.\r\n\r\nI do not necessarily see the need to expand the API, but maybe a config option could be useful.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5586/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5586/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}